Meeting Information


IEEE Computer Society 
AI and Smart Manufacturing 
Working Group Plenary Meeting

25-27 October 2019at CESI in Beijing, China

The IEEE Computer Society AI and Smart Manufacturing Working Group Plenary will be held Friday, 25 October 2019 through Sunday, 27 October 2019, at the China Electronic Standardization Institute (CESI) in Beijing, China. 

This meeting presents a great opportunity for all the Working Groups that are developing standards in similar technology areas to meet in parallel or succession and discuss potential coordination efforts, as well as bring potential participants into new working groups. 

For your reference, the 
following Working Groups will be in attendance:

IEEE P2671TM <http://go.standards.ieee.org/a0000D06NF0I00OLoY8f2wT>, Standard for General Requirements of Online Detection Based 
on Machine Vision in Intelligent Manufacturing
IEEE P2672TM <http://go.standards.ieee.org/y6fFINw80T0DLYp02P00000>, Guide for General Requirements of Mass Customization
IEEE P2806TM  <http://go.standards.ieee.org/SY0L0T0ID0208Fw0600fNQq>,System Architecture of Digital Representation for Physical Objects in Factory Environments
IEEE P2807TM <http://go.standards.ieee.org/p0200F06RL0N0r8YTD0wIf0>, Framework of Knowledge Graphs
IEEE P2807.1TM <http://go.standards.ieee.org/q6LF0T0IDS082f00Y0ws00N>, Standard for Technical Requirements and Evaluating Knowledge Graphs
IEEE P2830TM <http://go.standards.ieee.org/m0008T0020NT6DwIYft0FL0>, Standard for Technical Framework and Requirements of Shared Machine Learning
IEEE 
P2841 <http://go.standards.ieee.org/XTD0wUY08000Lf2IN006Fu0>TM <http://go.standards.ieee.org/XTD0wUY08000Lf2IN006Fu0>,Framework and Process for Deep Learning Evaluation
IEEE P3652.1TM <http://go.standards.ieee.org/K00N2FY00Dfv0VTIw0680L0>, Guide for Architectural Framework and Application of Federated Machine Learning

